{"symbol": "HMBS", "uniprot": "P08397", "protein_name": "Porphobilinogen deaminase", "length": 361, "function": "As part of the heme biosynthetic pathway, catalyzes the sequential polymerization of four molecules of porphobilinogen to form hydroxymethylbilane, also known as preuroporphyrinogen (PubMed:18004775, PubMed:18936296, PubMed:19138865, PubMed:23815679). Catalysis begins with the assembly of the dipyrromethane cofactor by the apoenzyme from two molecules of porphobilinogen or from preuroporphyrinogen. The covalently linked cofactor acts as a primer, around which the tetrapyrrole product is assembled (PubMed:18936296). In the last step of catalysis, the product, preuroporphyrinogen, is released, leaving the cofactor bound to the holodeaminase intact (PubMed:18936296)", "ensembl_gene": "ENSG00000256269", "scores": {"selectivity": 0.3499, "protein_drug": 0.678, "rna_drug": 0.258}, "flags": {"surface": false, "enzyme": true, "mod_aso": false, "mod_sirna": false}, "details": {"nominated_modality": "Small molecule", "winning_axis": "protein", "quadrant": "Protein-preferred", "best_route": "small molecule", "sm_score": "0.865", "sirna_score": "0.158", "aso_score": "0.165"}, "modality": "Small molecule", "structure": "data/structures/HMBS.pdb", "pockets": [{"rank": 1, "druggability": 0.511, "volume": 1423.0, "residues": [68, 69, 71, 72, 73, 74, 75, 76, 77, 78, 98, 99, 100, 101, 102, 103, 145, 146, 147, 148, 149, 150, 173, 214, 215, 217, 254, 259, 260, 261, 262, 263, 265, 359]}, {"rank": 2, "druggability": 0.013, "volume": 982.0, "residues": [26, 27, 28, 29, 30, 34, 57, 60, 61, 63, 64, 68, 77, 96, 98, 99, 150, 167, 168, 169, 170, 171, 172, 173, 188, 189, 191, 192, 195, 196, 216, 217, 218, 219]}, {"rank": 3, "druggability": 0.003, "volume": 431.5, "residues": [59, 79, 80, 82, 83, 86, 105, 106, 108]}], "links": [{"key": "uniprot", "label": "UniProt", "url": "https://www.uniprot.org/uniprotkb/P08397"}, {"key": "alphafold", "label": "AlphaFold", "url": "https://alphafold